BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Durham Geeks
UID:event_313858282@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260407T031307Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260408T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260408T203000
SUMMARY:Community Game Night at BoxyardRTP
DESCRIPTION:Durham Geeks\nEvery Wednesday at BoxYardRTP\, Matt hosts games
  from 5:30-8:30.\n\nBoxyardRTP is a collection of shipping containers used
  to create food and meeting spaces with a covered\, open-air common area w
 ith tables and chairs for eating\, playing games\, just sitting and talkin
 g\, or whatever you want. A few of the food areas have inside seating\, bu
 t the rest of the area is also dog-friendly. There is ample parking\, EV c
 harging\, and a free-play area for dogs.\n\nBoxyardRTP is located at 900 P
 ark Offices Drive.\n\nYou can find out more on their website.\n\nhttps:// 
 boxyard.rtp.org
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/durham-geeks/events/313858282/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260319T222642Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260319T222642Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Durham Geeks
UID:event_313875553@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260407T031307Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260409T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260409T233000
SUMMARY:Thursday Community Board Game night at Moondog Meadery
DESCRIPTION:Durham Geeks\nIn conjunction with Moon Dog Meadery\, we contin
 ue to have our Thursday Night Gaming Night from 7 until they kick us out. 
 It's a bit smaller group than the large Monday night extravaganza\, and th
 ere are a lot of drop in and independent groups here as well. Restaurants 
 are open on Thursdays\, so you can Dash you food right inside\, or bring i
 t with you!\n\nMoondog has an extensive and ever-changing collection of ga
 mes that are usually loaned out for a fee\, but on Thursdays (just like on
  Mondays)\, they are all free to play. Usually we can find folks to fill i
 n your table or teach you the basics of the games. I've been hosting it fo
 r a few months now\, and we have had a great time with students returning 
 and bringing in new colleagues\, as well as the faithful ones who attended
  over the summer.\n\nDogs and outside food both allowed and encouraged. Al
 ways free! There is award-winning mead on tap and bottled\, as well as an 
 ever-changing collection of beer\, cider\, THC-infused water\, colas and\,
  yes\, just plain old water to keep you hydrated on your adventure.\n\nAny
  questions? Contact us here at Durham Geeks!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/durham-geeks/events/313875553/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260321T001556Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260321T001556Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Durham Geeks
UID:event_313987399@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260407T031307Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260411T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260411T220000
SUMMARY:Twilight Imperium Game Day
DESCRIPTION:Durham Geeks\nFrom Wikipedia:\n[Twilight Imperium is a strateg
 y board game produced by Fantasy Flight Games and Asmodee in the genre of 
 science fiction and space opera. It was designed by Christian T. Petersen 
 and was first released in 1997. It is now in its fourth edition\, which ha
 s large changes over previous editions. It is known for the length of its 
 games and its in-depth strategy. As of 2024\, its compelling gameplay and 
 enduring popularity have seen it be hailed by Nerdist and Polygon as the "
 greatest board game ever made."](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twilight_Im
 perium)\n\nHere is your chance to play this epic adventure in an all-day e
 vent. There will be experienced players and newbies alike\, but all will b
 e welcomed to come and play! $25 advance ticket required. **Venmo™ @moon
 dogmeadery and put "T. I. 4" in the memo field.**\n\nHosted by MoonDog Mea
 dery. There will be pizza delivered midday\, which is included in your tic
 ket price. Drinks are available all day at regular prices. (Water bottles 
 and outside food are fine. No outside beverages\, please\, per Moondog pol
 icy.)\n\nWell-mannered dogs are always welcome at MoonDog!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/durham-geeks/events/313987399/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260327T205054Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260327T205054Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Durham Geeks
UID:event_314066113@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260407T031307Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T113000
SUMMARY:Durham Geeks: Community Clean Up
DESCRIPTION:Durham Geeks\nOur last litter cleanup was so much fun that we
 ’ve partnered with Keep Durham Beautiful to arrange a Durham Geeks exclu
 sive!\n\nWho: Any self-identifying geeks in the Durham tri-city area\nWhat
 : Picking up litter at Maplewood Cemetery\nWhere: We’ll meet in the Food
  Lion parking lot\, next to Lakewood Social\, and walk over to the cemeter
 y\, picking up errant trash along the way\nWhen: Sunday April 12\, 9:30-11
 :30am\nWhy: Great opportunity to thank and give back to the community that
  has hosted and supported our group all these years. (And who doesn’t lo
 ve a trash-free cemetery??)\n\nAll trash grabbers\, bags\, gloves and safe
 ty vests will be provided.\n\nRegister here:\nhttps://forms.gle/rSeuVHpTGo
 iDphuN7\n\nIf you’ve never gone trash-pickin’ with Courtney McGuire\, 
 you’re in for a treat! Join us and find out what all the buzz is about. 
 To double your entertainment value\, we’ll have you back in time to catc
 h games at Lakewood Social at noon!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/durham-geeks/events/314066113/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260401T025807Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260401T025807Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Durham Geeks
UID:event_314066145@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260407T031307Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T160000
SUMMARY:Sunday Community Game Day at Lakewood Social
DESCRIPTION:Durham Geeks\nWhat is up\, my fellow humans?! Need somewhere t
 o go or something to do this Sunday afternoon? How do some good games\, go
 od people\, and good food sound?? Good? I thought so. You want to be here!
 \n\nCome join us at Lakewood Social for some Sunday afternoon board gaming
  shenanigans! As always\, we always bring an egregious number of games\, s
 o feel free to come in and let us teach you something new! Even if you’r
 e new to board games or just want to try something new\, we will get you a
  seat and make sure you don’t have to stumble through a rulebook. Of cou
 rse\, you are more than welcome to bring a game of your own to play if you
 ’re a seasoned gamer (or just really love that ONE game!) we will get it
  to the table!\n\nLakewood Social offers a great selection of delicious gr
 ub and a huge variety of beverages to choose from\, no matter what your ta
 ste. They have plenty of table space as well as space to get up and move a
 round! It is going to be all around a pretty great time!! Not to mention t
 hat we have a great group of friends that will make you feel right at home
 ! So come on out and let's show Lakewood some of that good Durham Game Com
 munity LOVE!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/durham-geeks/events/314066145/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260401T030201Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260401T030201Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Durham Geeks
UID:event_314066156@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260407T031307Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T150000
SUMMARY:Board game designers meetup at Lakewood Social!
DESCRIPTION:Durham Geeks\nLocal board game designers meetup at Lakewood So
 cial! This will be a no pressure side meetup at Lakewood Social in tandem 
 with our normal game day to toss around some ideas and playtest some new g
 ames! Even if you have no desire to be published\, or even finish a game\,
  this is a good place to just toss around ideas and meet some new gamers!\
 n\nThere will also be the normal group of gamers so feel free to join us f
 or some games while your'e there!\n\nHope to see y'all there!!!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/durham-geeks/events/314066156/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260401T030301Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260401T030301Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Durham Geeks
UID:event_313934418@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260407T031307Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260413T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260413T230000
SUMMARY:Weekly Game Night!
DESCRIPTION:Durham Geeks\nWe meet at Moon Dog Meadery under Joe Van Gogh o
 n Broad Street every Monday night. We have loads of games (some belong to 
 MoonDog\, some are brought by attendees)\, a fun and welcoming group of fo
 lks (always eager to have more\, however!)\, and there are always folks ea
 ger to teach games to those who haven't played certain titles.\n\nMoondog 
 has a growing collection of canned and bottled brews\, ciders\, and colas 
 in addition to their in-house-brewed meads. There are also some snacks lik
 e chips and popcorn. Sometimes\, folks bring in other treats to share. If 
 you do\, please mark them as containing any common allergens.\n\nOutside f
 ood (delivered\, brought in\, or homemade) is welcomed and encouraged. Out
 side drinks are not. Since the venue does not prepare food\, **dogs are al
 lowed and welcomed.** (Dogs are very friendly and welcoming\, too\, but th
 ey mostly roam around to collect ear scritches and love. If you're not com
 fortable with dogs around\, let us know\, and we'll try to accommodate.)\n
 \nBring games\, friends\, and a welcoming spirit. We're excited to have yo
 u with us!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/durham-geeks/events/313934418/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260324T234407Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260324T234407Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
